--- !u!114 &3000007
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 3000001}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2ea6422d1962ba3409655b2a2dc99dff, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Mossmark.Prototype4.AcquaintableAttendable
  entityId: p4_netmender
  unfamiliarShortName: Someone
  unfamiliarDescription: Someone bent over work you can't make out, their back half
    to the path.
  unfamiliarTint: {r: 0.45, g: 0.45, b: 0.45, a: 1}
  unfamiliarInteractionLine: Hold E to watch a while
  seededPropertyIds:
  - binds_fast
  seededKnowledgeLead: They speak of
  trueStateNote: mends eel traps for three households; hands slowing; teaching no
    one
  acquaintanceStages:
  - stageId: acquainted
    stageDisplayName: Acquainted
    attendsCost: 2
    shortName: A netmender
    description: "A mender of nets — traps too, by the shapes drying on the rail.
      Old work, sure work. They nod when you come up the path now."
    tint: {r: 0.52, g: 0.55, b: 0.45, a: 1}
    interactionLine: Hold E to spend a while with them
    attendFlavors:
    - They work on without minding you. Once, they angle a knot toward the light,
      as if you'd asked.
  - stageId: known
    stageDisplayName: Known
    attendsCost: 3
    shortName: The Netmender
    description: The netmender who was the ferryman here, before the rope went.
      Three households still eat out of these traps. The hands are slowing; nobody
      is learning the knots.
    tint: {r: 0.45, g: 0.62, b: 0.4, a: 1}
    interactionLine: Hold E to pass a while with them
    attendFlavors:
    - They glance up and go back to the knots. The silence is an easy one now.
    - "They hold a trap out for you to see — where it wore through, and where
      it was mended."
  attendDuration: 2
  unfamiliarAttendFlavors:
  - You watch a while. The work goes on; nothing gives itself away.
  - Hands moving, something turned and turned again. You couldn't say what.
